snippet.textDisplay:
This is only in regards to the first question asked.
It seems the reporter wants to know how accurate was his performance in regards to mental illness.
Really, you want to know how accurate is a stage(d) act to reality.
Why. For if you want realisim, go actually spend time with actual sufferers of mental problems.

Society applauds actor for realistic performance.
Actual sufferer is ignored and looked down upon by society. (not by everyone of course, but you get my meaning)

What I continue to find irrational about many folks regarding entertainment.
Folks will immerse themselves in fake dramas, and be enlivened by it, but will ignore the real ones, especially their own.

Wanna experience an exceptional story. Go help real sufferers or all kinds of problems, and change their lives for the better. End credits. A good feeling is retained by all, for far longer than one obtained by experiencing a good movie or tv show.

And the best story to be involved in, is your own. Nothing beats a hero's quest movie more than an actual personal story of overcoming some life threatening or damaging condition, or of helping a real person to do so.
